Java 21 Features (LTS) ⭐ Interview Important + Examples

Java 21 is a Long-Term Support (LTS) release and one of the most important versions for Spring Boot + enterprise systems.

1. Virtual Threads (Final Feature) ⭐⭐⭐

Virtual threads are lightweight threads designed for high concurrency with low memory usage.

Example
public class VirtualThreadExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Thread.startVirtualThread(() -> {

            System.out.println("Virtual Thread Running");
        });
    }
}
Real-Time Use Case
Banking System / E-commerce:
- 1 million requests
- Traditional threads → heavy memory
- Virtual threads → lightweight, scalable
Benefits

✔ Handles millions of threads
✔ Low memory usage
✔ Ideal for microservices

2. Pattern Matching for switch (Finalized) ⭐

Simplifies type-based logic.

Example
static String process(Object obj) {

    return switch (obj) {

        case String s ->
                "String: " + s;

        case Integer i ->
                "Integer: " + i;

        case Double d ->
                "Double: " + d;

        default ->
                "Unknown Type";
    };
}
Output
String: Java
Integer: 100
Benefits

✔ No instanceof checks
✔ Cleaner code
✔ More readable switch

3. Record Patterns (Final Feature) ⭐

Used to deconstruct records directly.

Example
record Employee(int id, String name) {}

static void print(Object obj) {

    if (obj instanceof Employee(int id, String name)) {

        System.out.println(id);
        System.out.println(name);
    }
}
Output
101
Sunil
Benefits

✔ Easy data extraction
✔ Works with pattern matching
✔ Less boilerplate

4. Sequenced Collections ⭐

New interfaces to maintain ordered collections with predictable navigation.

Example
SequencedCollection<String> list =
        new ArrayList<>();

list.add("A");
list.add("B");
list.add("C");

System.out.println(list.getFirst());
System.out.println(list.getLast());
Output
A
C
Benefits

✔ Easy access to first/last elements
✔ Better collection consistency

5. String Templates (Preview)

Used for cleaner string building (like interpolation).

Example
String name = "Sunil";
int age = 25;

String result = STR."Name: \{name}, Age: \{age}";

System.out.println(result);
Output
Name: Sunil, Age: 25
6. Unnamed Variables & Patterns

Used to ignore unused variables.

Example
try {
    int x = 10;
} catch (Exception _) {
    System.out.println("Error ignored");
}
Benefits

✔ Cleaner code
✔ Avoid unused variable warnings

7. Structured Concurrency (Preview)

Improves multi-thread task handling.

Example
try (var scope =
        new StructuredTaskScope.ShutdownOnFailure()) {

    var task1 = scope.fork(() -> "Task1");
    var task2 = scope.fork(() -> "Task2");

    scope.join();

    System.out.println(task1.get());
    System.out.println(task2.get());
}
Benefits

✔ Manage multiple threads easily
✔ Better error handling
✔ Cleaner async code

Real-Time Example (Spring Boot + Java 21)
Virtual Threads in Controller
@GetMapping("/process")
public String process() {

    Thread.startVirtualThread(() -> {

        System.out.println("Processing request");
    });

    return "Request Accepted";
}
Benefit
Handles thousands of requests efficiently without blocking server threads
